  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "Inverting a selection in Photoshop is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Open your image** in Photoshop.\n2. **Make a selection** using any of the selection tools (e.g., Marquee Tool, Lasso Tool, Magic Wand Tool).\n3. **Invert the selection**:\n   - Go to the **Select menu** at the top of the screen.\n   - Click on **Inverse**.\n\nAlternatively, you can use the shortcut `Shift + Ctrl + I` (Windows) or `Shift + Command + I` (Mac).\n\nThis action will invert your current selection, selecting everything outside of the original selection area while deselecting the original area.",
